  "description": [
    "iROKER LAUDS LOEWS ACTION N Y Broker Declares Public Ownership is Sign of The Times PRINCIPLE IS ECONOMIC Also Sees in It Formidable Weapon in Combating Bolshevism Financial circles in Washington are entirely familiar with Marcus Loews offer of stock to his theater patrons at 22 per share payable 4 down and 3 a month for six months Few perhaps appreciate however the full significance of Loews offer Few perhaps see in this a trend which is shaping up on the part of big businesses toward greater public ownership Aj prominent New York broker in town yesterday when approached regarding Loews latest action J commented as follows This move on the part of Marcus Loew is a sign of the times More and more we see the people of this country taking the ownership of our important businesses out of Wall Street into their safe deposit boxes More and more we find ourselves progressing toward that goal of cooperative business where the uer and consumer of the products of industry gets back part of what he pays in the form of dividends on his investments This is the true and sound economic principle of cooperative business Take the case in"
